def selection_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n):
        min_idx = i
        for j in range(i+1, n):
            if arr[j] < arr[min_idx]:
                min_idx = j
        arr[i], arr[min_idx] = arr[min_idx], arr[i]
    return arr
```

This corrected version uses two nested loops to find the minimum element from the unsorted part of the array and swap it with the first unsorted element. This process is repeated until the entire array is sorted.
